# ai-coding-workflows

A tiny CLI to scaffold AI coding workflow docs and help generate git commit messages locally.

## Features

- Create a starter `workflows/` folder with Prompts, Instructions, Tool Sets, Modes, and MCP Servers docs.
- Generate conventional-style commit messages from staged changes.
- Optional `prepare-commit-msg` hook to auto-fill empty commit messages.

## Install

Editable install in this repo:

```bash
pip install -e .
```

## Usage

Scaffold a workflows directory:

```bash
aiwf generate -o workflows
```

Generate an AI-assisted commit message (print only):

```bash
aiwf ai-commit --print --conventional
```

Commit with AI-generated message:

```bash
git add -A
aiwf ai-commit --conventional
```

Install a git hook to auto-fill empty commit messages:

```bash
aiwf install-hook
```

## Notes

This tool intentionally uses local heuristics only (no network calls or real AI) to keep it simple and offline-friendly. You can extend `ai_workflows/git_ai.py` to call your preferred LLM if desired.



